    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-06-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="215" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d215">
                <head>No. 928.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Lewis</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-06-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 4,
                            1888</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 78.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your attention is recalled to my No. 68 of
                        December 7 last concerning the complaint of F. C. Butman, of Boston,
                        alleging discrimination by the Portuguese Government against the direct
                        trade between the United States and the Cape Verde Islands as compared with
                        that passing <hi rend="italic">via</hi> Lisbon.</p>
                <p>The Department desires to receive as soon as possible the report which my No.
                        68 instructs you to make.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
